<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="734" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="26.[1463,2667,1703,2405]" pageId="26" pageNumber="734">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1464,1818,2137,2170]" pageId="26" pageNumber="734">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Inornate Squirrel is widely distributed, has a presumed large population, occurs in a number of protected areas, and tolerates some degree of habitat modification. It is hunted in Laos, but there is no evidence that this poses a threat. Habitat loss may not be a threat as it may actually benefit from shifting agriculture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
